'''梗阻性尿路症'''({{lang|en|Obstructive uropathy}})是正常[[尿|尿]]液流動的結構或功能障礙，<ref>Definition:  [http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/000507.htm/ obstructive uropathy from Online Medical Dictionary.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/000507.htm/ |date=20150105042651 }}</ref>有時導致腎功能不全(梗阻性[[腎病|腎病]])。

這是一個非常寬泛的術語，並不意味著位置或[[原因論|病因]]。

==病因==
{{seealso|腎功能|腎生理學}}

它可以由[[泌尿系統|尿道]]的任一點病變所引起。<ref>{{Cite book | author=Kumar, Vinay; Fausto, Nelson; Fausto, Nelso; Robbins, Stanley L.; Abbas, Abul K.; Cotran, Ramzi S. | authorlink= | title=Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease | year=2005 | edition=7th| publisher=Elsevier Saunders | location=Philadelphia, Pa. | isbn=0-7216-0187-1 | pages=1012}}</ref>

原因有[[尿路結石|尿路結石]](Urolithiasis)，<ref name="pmid18818145">{{cite journal |author=Tsai PJ, Lin JT, Wu TT, Tsai CC |title=Ureterosciatic hernia causes obstructive uropathy |journal=J Chin Med Assoc |volume=71 |issue=9 |pages=491–3 |date=September 2008 |pmid=18818145 |doi= 10.1016/S1726-4901(08)70155-2|url=http://ajws.elsevier.com/ajws_pubmed/pubmed_switch.asp?journal_issn=1726-4901&art_pub_year=2008&%20art_pub_month=09&art_pub_vol=71&art_sp=491 |format=}} {{dead link|date=May 2010}}</ref>"後尿道瓣膜"(posterior urethral valve)及"輸尿管疝"(ureteral herniation)。<ref name="pmid18818145"/>

==症狀==
症狀、不太可能是慢性阻塞，而是疼痛放射到T11到T12的[[皮節|皮節]]（Dermatome）、{{le|無尿症|Anuria|無尿}}(anuria)、[[夜尿症|夜尿]]、或[[多尿症|多尿]]。

==診斷==<!--
Diagnosis is based on results of bladder [[catheterization|catheterization]], [[ultrasonography|ultrasonography]], [[CT_scan|CT scan]], [[Cystoscopy|cystourethroscopy]], or [[pyelography|pyelography]], depending on the level of obstruction.-->

==治療==<!--
Treatment, depending on cause, may require prompt drainage of the [[urinary_bladder|bladder]] via [[urinary_catheterization|catheterization]], medical instrumentation, surgery (e.g. [[endoscopy|endoscopy]], [[lithotripsy|lithotripsy]]), [[hormonal_therapy|hormonal therapy]], or a combination of these modalities.

Treatment of the obstruction at the level of the ureter:
:* Open surgery.
:* Less invasive treatment: laparoscopic correction. 
:* Minimal invasive treament: Overtoom procedure:<ref>[http://www.overtoomballoon.com/attachments/article/4/Artikel%20AJR%20april%202009.pdf Treatment of ureteropelvic junction obstruction using a detachable inflatable stent: initial experience] {{Wayback|url=http://www.overtoomballoon.com/attachments/article/4/Artikel%20AJR%20april%202009.pdf |date=20140109113917 }} by Timotheus T C Overtoom, Peter L Vijverberg, Hendrik W van Es, Sandrine van Selm, Hans P M van Heesewijk</ref> dilatation with cutting [[balloon_catheter|balloon catheter]] (e.g. Boston Scientific) followed by introduction of the [[ureteric_balloon_catheter|pyeloplasty balloon catheter]].<ref>[http://www.overtoomballoon.com Pyeloplasty balloon catheter]</ref> This balloon is inflated with pure contrast agent via the pusher and remains in situ in the ureter to keep the previous treated stricture dilated while the expanded [[urothelium|urothelium]] heals. Urine can drain through the central channel of this catheter.-->

